---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Play"
  description="Play GridPonder puzzle games in your browser, or learn how to create your own."
>
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">
    <div class="mb-10">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Play GridPonder</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-500 text-lg">All puzzle packs run directly in your browser. No installation needed.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-12 items-start">

      <!-- Phone frame with game -->
      <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-4">
        <div class="phone-frame">
          <iframe
            src="/game/"
            class="phone-screen"
            width="390"
            height="760"
            title="GridPonder game"
            loading="lazy"
            allow="fullscreen"
          ></iframe>
        </div>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 text-center max-w-[390px]">
          Tip: works best on a phone. Install the app for the native experience.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Right panel -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-10 lg:pt-4">

        <!-- App store links -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">Native App</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mb-5">
            A native iOS and Android app is planned. Stay tuned.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
            <!-- Google Play badge -->
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-xl px-5 py-3 opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed select-none">
              <svg class="w-7 h-7" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor"><path d="M3.18 23.76c.33.19.7.24 1.07.14l12.6-12.6-2.85-2.84L3.18 23.76zM20.69 10.37l-2.44-1.41-3.19 3.19 3.19 3.19 2.45-1.41c.7-.4.7-1.56-.01-1.56zM4.25.1C3.88 0 3.51.05 3.18.24L14 11.06l3.05-3.06L4.25.1zM2.82 1.05C2.31 1.5 2 2.22 2 3.1v17.8c0 .88.31 1.6.82 2.05l.12.1 9.97-9.97v-.22L2.94.95l-.12.1z"/></svg>
              <div>
                <div class="text-xs text-gray-400">Coming to</div>
                <div class="text-sm font-semibold">Google Play</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <!-- App Store badge -->
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 bg-gray-900 text-white rounded-xl px-5 py-3 opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed select-none">
              <svg class="w-7 h-7" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor"><path d="M18.71 19.5c-.83 1.24-1.71 2.45-3.05 2.47-1.34.03-1.77-.79-3.29-.79-1.53 0-2 .77-3.27.82-1.31.05-2.3-1.32-3.14-2.53C4.25 17 2.94 12.45 4.7 9.39c.87-1.52 2.43-2.48 4.12-2.51 1.28-.02 2.5.87 3.29.87.78 0 2.26-1.07 3.8-.91.65.03 2.47.26 3.64 1.98-.09.06-2.17 1.28-2.15 3.81.03 3.02 2.65 4.03 2.68 4.04-.03.07-.42 1.44-1.38 2.83M13 3.5c.73-.83 1.94-1.46 2.94-1.5.13 1.17-.34 2.35-1.04 3.19-.69.85-1.83 1.51-2.95 1.42-.15-1.15.41-2.35 1.05-3.11z"/></svg>
              <div>
                <div class="text-xs text-gray-400">Coming to</div>
                <div class="text-sm font-semibold">App Store</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Creator guide -->
        <div id="create">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">Create Your Own Game</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mb-6">
            Games are pure data — JSON files that describe a board, entities, and rules.
            An AI assistant guides you interactively from idea to a playable pack.
          </p>

          <ol class="space-y-5">
            {[
              {
                step: 1,
                title: 'Clone the repository',
                code: 'git clone https://github.com/Gridponder/platform',
                note: undefined,
              },
              {
                step: 2,
                title: 'Install Claude Code',
                code: 'npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code',
                note: 'Or another AI coding assistant that supports slash commands.',
              },
              {
                step: 3,
                title: 'Open a game directory and start Claude',
                code: 'cd platform && claude',
                note: undefined,
              },
              {
                step: 4,
                title: 'Type the create-game command',
                code: '/create-game',
                note: 'Claude guides you through naming, mechanics, entities, levels, and theming — all interactively.',
              },
              {
                step: 5,
                title: 'Zip and share',
                code: 'zip -r my-game.zip packs/my-game/',
                note: 'Send the zip to anyone with the GridPonder app. They can import it directly.',
              },
              {
                step: 6,
                title: 'Submit to the main repo',
                code: undefined,
                note: 'If your game is well-crafted and broadly appealing, open a GitHub issue or ping @jens to get it included in the official pack list.',
              },
            ].map(({ step, title, code, note }) => (
              <li class="flex gap-4">
                <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-brand-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold">
                  {step}
                </div>
                <div class="flex-1 min-w-0 pt-0.5">
                  <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">{title}</p>
                  {code && (
                    <code class="block bg-gray-900 text-green-400 font-mono text-sm px-4 py-2 rounded-lg mb-2 overflow-x-auto">
                      {code}
                    </code>
                  )}
                  {note && <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">{note}</p>}
                </div>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ol>

          <div class="mt-8 p-4 bg-brand-50 border border-brand-100 rounded-xl">
            <p class="text-sm text-brand-800">
              <span class="font-semibold">Game packs are data, not code.</span>
              The engine is fixed and sandboxed — imported packs cannot execute arbitrary code
              and are safe to share with anyone.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
